1
00:00:12,080 --> 00:00:13,775
But if we...

2
00:00:33,401 --> 00:00:36,529
- But how can?
- Jesus Christ.

3
00:00:37,305 --> 00:00:38,795
So this means that...

4
00:00:42,477 --> 00:00:45,378
- What?
- So no one killed any homeless men.

5
00:00:45,413 --> 00:00:47,142
No serial killer.

6
00:00:48,616 --> 00:00:50,277
Some were random killings,

7
00:00:50,318 --> 00:00:53,082
some were natural deaths
that were likely manipulated.

8
00:00:53,121 --> 00:00:55,612
- But they're not linked in any way.
- But why?

9
00:00:55,657 --> 00:00:59,024
The detectives used the money to fund a case
against the drug traffickers responsible

10
00:00:59,060 --> 00:01:00,721
for the slayings in the vacants a year ago.

11
00:01:00,762 --> 00:01:03,526
Last week's arrests and seizures
were a direct result.

12
00:01:03,565 --> 00:01:06,557
So let me just understand this.

13
00:01:09,370 --> 00:01:11,861
So I've been going out there for weeks,

14
00:01:11,906 --> 00:01:14,568
slamming the Governor
for his neglect of the homeless

15
00:01:14,609 --> 00:01:16,270
and declaring how we will stop at nothing

16
00:01:16,311 --> 00:01:18,973
to find the person responsible
for preying on the homeless

17
00:01:19,013 --> 00:01:22,210
and all the while...
Hey, Norman, this is my ass here.

18
00:01:22,250 --> 00:01:24,616
That's true, boss.

19
00:01:24,652 --> 00:01:26,847
But it does have a certain charm to it.

20
00:01:27,288 --> 00:01:29,518
They manufactured an issue to get paid,

21
00:01:29,557 --> 00:01:33,220
we manufactured an issue
to get you elected governor.

22
00:01:33,261 --> 00:01:37,595
Everybody's getting what they need
behind some make-believe.

23
00:01:37,632 --> 00:01:41,295
The detectives involved will be suspended
and ultimately fired, at the least.

24
00:01:41,336 --> 00:01:45,500
Beyond that, a criminal prosecution
on fraud and perjury charges is probable.

25
00:01:45,540 --> 00:01:47,667
You're saying
we call a press conference and we say,

26
00:01:47,709 --> 00:01:50,439
"By the way, all that stuff
about homeless people getting killed

27
00:01:50,478 --> 00:01:52,742
"and the Governor cutting the safety net

28
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:55,806
"and us doing everything
in our power to catch the guy,

29
00:01:55,850 --> 00:02:00,253
- "guess what, the joke's on us?"
- Not to mention that the evidence

30
00:02:00,288 --> 00:02:03,553
against the traffickers
arrested last week is tainted.

31
00:02:03,591 --> 00:02:05,684
That case could collapse as well.

32
00:02:05,727 --> 00:02:07,752
I don't fucking believe this.

33
00:02:08,930 --> 00:02:10,522
You two are on point here.

34
00:02:10,565 --> 00:02:13,227
Word of this gets down to Annapolis,
the Governor's gonna wreck me with it.

35
00:02:13,267 --> 00:02:16,703
And if it comes to that,
you guys drop on your swords, so help me.

36
00:02:16,738 --> 00:02:21,004
How does word not get out
once we suspend the detectives?

37
00:02:21,042 --> 00:02:24,239
Never mind sending it to the grand jury
for a criminal case?

38
00:02:24,278 --> 00:02:28,908
The cops that did this, they gotta go. You
cannot be telling me I have to live with this.

39
00:02:28,950 --> 00:02:31,043
Deputy, Counselor...

40
00:02:32,053 --> 00:02:34,578
if you two will excuse us,
we are going to discuss this first

41
00:02:34,622 --> 00:02:36,590
as a matter of public policy.

42
00:02:42,296 --> 00:02:45,094
If this becomes public in the wrong way,

43
00:02:45,133 --> 00:02:47,897
a lot of people who were legally responsible
for the situation,

44
00:02:47,935 --> 00:02:51,598
good people who were, nonetheless,
in a supervisory role here...

45
00:02:52,273 --> 00:02:53,900
are going to suffer.

46
00:02:53,941 --> 00:02:56,637
And that's not the outcome
that anyone wants.

47
00:02:57,912 --> 00:03:01,575
What Mike is saying is that we need to be
very careful about how to proceed.

48
00:03:11,993 --> 00:03:15,656
I wish I was still at the newspaper
so I could write on this mess.

49
00:03:17,165 --> 00:03:19,156
It's too fucking good.

50
00:05:10,611 --> 00:05:13,079
Lester. What brings you down?

51
00:05:13,114 --> 00:05:16,777
We don't have anything scheduled
from you today, I don't think...

52
00:05:22,623 --> 00:05:25,387
40,000 from the Showboat on the boardwalk.

53
00:05:25,426 --> 00:05:27,417
26 at the Borgata.

54
00:05:28,863 --> 00:05:30,922
80 over the last year at the Taj Mahal

55
00:05:30,965 --> 00:05:33,559
and that's just the Atlantic City casinos.

56
00:05:34,535 --> 00:05:36,400
I like to play. So what?

57
00:05:36,437 --> 00:05:39,770
You lost three times your salary
over the last two years.

58
00:05:41,342 --> 00:05:45,108
I ran you through Sentinel Title
and came back with seven pages of liens

59
00:05:45,146 --> 00:05:48,673
and a third mortgage you folded on
two months ago.

60
00:05:49,383 --> 00:05:51,112
Gary, you're done.

61
00:05:51,686 --> 00:05:52,914
What do you mean?

62
00:05:52,954 --> 00:05:56,446
We found sealed grand jury papers
in the houses of drug dealers

63
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:58,481
and we've got people naming you on it.

64
00:06:01,295 --> 00:06:03,320
You have a problem, Gary.

65
00:06:04,565 --> 00:06:08,501
But you have friends in this courthouse,
lifelong friends.

66
00:06:08,536 --> 00:06:12,734
Cop to the problem, give up the names
of those that bought from you.

67
00:06:12,773 --> 00:06:14,764
Disbarred? Yeah, no doubt.

68
00:06:15,476 --> 00:06:17,876
But you play it clean from this moment on

69
00:06:18,579 --> 00:06:20,672
and we both know you'll probably walk.

70
00:06:22,717 --> 00:06:25,185
- Why did you look at me?
- I ran the finances

71
00:06:25,219 --> 00:06:27,687
on everyone who worked this unit
over the last couple years.

72
00:06:27,722 --> 00:06:30,748
You were the only bogie.
If the S.A.O. Weren't so screwed up,

73
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:33,521
they'd have been running
background checks as a routine.

74
00:06:33,561 --> 00:06:35,153
But I guess you knew that.

75
00:06:36,564 --> 00:06:39,658
I always wondered
if they'd get their shit together.

76
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:41,634
But that's Baltimore, isn't it?

77
00:06:45,206 --> 00:06:47,504
So what happens now?

78
00:06:47,541 --> 00:06:49,236
Well, for starters...

79
00:06:53,848 --> 00:06:55,839
you're gonna make a phone call.

80
00:06:57,818 --> 00:07:01,515
McNulty, Freamon, Sydnor...

81
00:07:01,555 --> 00:07:04,285
Any one who has the smell
of this on them should be gone.

82
00:07:04,325 --> 00:07:06,452
Before the close of business,
they should be suspended

83
00:07:06,494 --> 00:07:07,893
and, before the end
of the week, indicted.

84
00:07:07,929 --> 00:07:10,056
- I know, but...
- But what?

85
00:07:10,097 --> 00:07:13,294
We're gonna let this shit stand
because it'll hurt Carcetti to air it out?

86
00:07:13,334 --> 00:07:16,929
Instead of cleaning house like we need to,
he's up there figuring out how to hide the dirt.

87
00:07:16,971 --> 00:07:19,963
I got a mind to call the Governor myself
and just let it fly.

88
00:07:20,007 --> 00:07:22,441
- Cedric, you can't.
- Why not?

89
00:07:22,476 --> 00:07:25,536
If I let this thing stand, I might as well
just roll over and play dead

90
00:07:25,579 --> 00:07:27,570
for every police who knows about this.

91
00:07:30,117 --> 00:07:33,985
- We cover this up...
- Cedric, you can't do anything.

92
00:07:34,021 --> 00:07:35,420
Those are your detectives.

93
00:07:35,456 --> 00:07:37,890
They need someone to blame,
they will measure you for it.

94
00:07:37,925 --> 00:07:39,790
I don't give a fuck.

95
00:07:42,663 --> 00:07:44,597
And they'll fire me.

96
00:07:49,403 --> 00:07:51,371
You heard Steintorf.

97
00:07:53,774 --> 00:07:55,469
I was in charge of this thing.

98
00:07:55,509 --> 00:07:57,704
I was on that wiretap.

99
00:08:00,281 --> 00:08:02,613
This is my career.
This is everything.

100
00:08:07,621 --> 00:08:11,614
You go public and it hurts Carcetti.

101
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:16,963
Maybe he doesn't get to be governor
but he is still the Mayor,

102
00:08:16,998 --> 00:08:19,057
and Bond is still my boss,

103
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:21,568
and you know the weight will not fall on them.

104
00:08:21,602 --> 00:08:23,661
- It never does.
- Christ.

105
00:08:25,706 --> 00:08:29,540
Everything I worked for, all those years
in that courthouse...

106
00:08:36,484 --> 00:08:38,179
Please.

107
00:08:40,888 --> 00:08:42,651
25 cents. Baltimore Sun.

108
00:08:44,158 --> 00:08:45,989
Sir, Baltimore Sun. One quarter.

109
00:08:47,762 --> 00:08:49,753
- Keep it.
- Thank you, sir. Thank you.

110
00:08:55,936 --> 00:08:58,029
People tip pretty good, don't they?

111
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:01,540
"...paying him for what he had done to us.

112
00:09:01,575 --> 00:09:03,202
"I'm sorry for him, man, really,

113
00:09:03,244 --> 00:09:06,236
"but I still can't let him come up
from the basement."

114
00:09:09,617 --> 00:09:13,417
- You gonna put all that in the paper?
- That's the plan.

115
00:09:14,021 --> 00:09:16,455
Even the parts about Sherrod?

116
00:09:16,490 --> 00:09:18,082
Yeah.

117
00:09:21,462 --> 00:09:25,262
- What good is a story like that?
- Like what?

118
00:09:25,299 --> 00:09:27,267
Like me, Sherrod.
Gettin' high. Not gettin' high.

119
00:09:27,301 --> 00:09:28,962
My sister, all that shit in there.

120
00:09:29,003 --> 00:09:31,335
What good do any of that
do to put it in the newspaper?

121
00:09:31,372 --> 00:09:34,864
People read it, they think about it.
Maybe see things different.

122
00:09:34,909 --> 00:09:36,376
I don't know, man.

123
00:09:36,410 --> 00:09:39,243
Bubs, you don't want me
to do this, I won't do it.

124
00:09:42,349 --> 00:09:44,340
I don't know.

125
00:09:44,819 --> 00:09:48,346
Baltimore Sun. A little bit of sun. Sun paper.

126
00:09:48,389 --> 00:09:50,880
Look, Rupert, go public
with this thing if you want

127
00:09:50,925 --> 00:09:53,985
but your shop is gonna come out looking worse
for letting it happen in the first place.

128
00:09:54,028 --> 00:09:56,019
The better move is to shut it down quietly

129
00:09:56,063 --> 00:09:59,328
and then deal with those responsible
through back channels.

130
00:09:59,366 --> 00:10:02,358
We'll bury these guys softly
and in a hole so deep

131
00:10:02,403 --> 00:10:04,837
no one will ever get close
to digging them up.

132
00:10:08,542 --> 00:10:10,533
I can see that.

133
00:10:10,578 --> 00:10:13,046
Commissioner, do you agree?

134
00:10:14,181 --> 00:10:16,649
Well, it is a little more problematic for me.

135
00:10:17,585 --> 00:10:20,076
The offenders are in my shop,
are they not?

136
00:10:22,623 --> 00:10:25,091
Can I have a word with you in private, Bill?

137
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:30,025
Hey, if Rawls isn't in, I'm not either.

138
00:10:30,064 --> 00:10:32,532
I wouldn't worry about Bill Rawls.

139
00:10:32,566 --> 00:10:37,128
I believe he's about to have
one of those road to Damascus moments.

140
00:10:39,039 --> 00:10:41,030
I can see what you're thinking in there.

141
00:10:41,075 --> 00:10:44,306
I can see the gears grinding
in that head of yours.

142
00:10:47,481 --> 00:10:51,042
You're thinking, "Hey,
I might have some wood on Carcetti here.

143
00:10:51,085 --> 00:10:53,451
"There's no way they can
pin the blame on me for this fiasco

144
00:10:53,487 --> 00:10:57,116
"without doing their boy Daniels, too."
You're thinking we'd have to fire Daniels

145
00:10:57,158 --> 00:11:01,288
to fire you and that wouldn't sit well,
given how much we've already sold Daniels.

146
00:11:01,328 --> 00:11:03,193
Isn't that what you're thinking?

147
00:11:03,230 --> 00:11:06,165
You're telling yourself maybe
there's a way for you to leverage this,

148
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:08,464
to get yourself a full term as commissioner,

149
00:11:08,502 --> 00:11:12,029
to delay Daniels a few more years
in exchange for you shutting the fuck up

150
00:11:12,072 --> 00:11:13,801
and doing what you're told.

151
00:11:13,841 --> 00:11:16,105
And you know what, Bill?
You're not far off.

152
00:11:16,143 --> 00:11:19,169
You do have a little leverage here
but just a little.

153
00:11:19,213 --> 00:11:20,976
I wouldn't overplay your hand.

154
00:11:21,982 --> 00:11:23,574
How would you play it?

155
00:11:23,617 --> 00:11:25,482
I'd shut the fuck up and wait your turn

156
00:11:25,519 --> 00:11:28,386
and, when Tommy gets to the statehouse,
he brings you with him

157
00:11:28,422 --> 00:11:30,413
to be State Police Superintendent.

158
00:11:30,457 --> 00:11:33,722
Because while you may be a shade too white

159
00:11:33,761 --> 00:11:35,752
to run the Baltimore department,

160
00:11:35,796 --> 00:11:37,991
you're just about right for the M.S.P.

161
00:11:43,003 --> 00:11:45,631
- I have your word?
- And I have yours.

162
00:11:56,217 --> 00:11:58,014
Back channel is the way to go.

163
00:11:58,052 --> 00:12:02,182
See? The Police Commissioner
done fell off his ass.

164
00:12:08,562 --> 00:12:10,291
Can I help you?

165
00:12:11,865 --> 00:12:13,526
I need to see Mr. Prezbo.

166
00:12:14,668 --> 00:12:16,568
Someone will come down.

167
00:12:37,558 --> 00:12:40,857
- Are you a student here?
- Ms. Donnelly, it's me, Duquan.

168
00:12:42,029 --> 00:12:44,657
It's good to see you but
you're not a student here

169
00:12:44,698 --> 00:12:46,962
so I can't let you inside.

170
00:12:47,001 --> 00:12:49,526
I just came past to see Mr. Prezbo.

171
00:12:49,570 --> 00:12:51,231
Well, he's teaching right now.

172
00:12:51,272 --> 00:12:53,331
I know. I can wait.

173
00:12:54,508 --> 00:12:56,373
You're gonna have to stay outside.

174
00:12:56,410 --> 00:12:59,868
After the bell, I'll tell Mr. Pryzbylewski
you're out here for him, OK?

175
00:13:10,491 --> 00:13:12,959
I'm going to surprise you with something.

176
00:13:12,993 --> 00:13:14,517
You already have.

177
00:13:14,895 --> 00:13:19,559
I got a tip from an informant
about a leak out of the grand jury unit.

178
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,591
Sad to say it's checked out.

179
00:13:21,635 --> 00:13:24,763
- We know about the leak.
- But do you know who it is?

180
00:13:24,805 --> 00:13:26,534
Gary diPasquale.

181
00:13:27,174 --> 00:13:30,143
Decent enough guy but he's got
a bear of a gambling problem

182
00:13:30,177 --> 00:13:33,442
and a bank of drug lawyers
who are willing to pay for their look-sees.

183
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:36,142
Troy Sanders, Marvin Bronfman,

184
00:13:36,183 --> 00:13:39,209
Dennis Cray, Sid Silverstein.

185
00:13:39,253 --> 00:13:42,051
And the pick of the litter? Maurice Levy.

186
00:13:43,924 --> 00:13:45,687
I kid you not.

187
00:13:45,726 --> 00:13:47,387
Gary is their leak?

188
00:13:47,428 --> 00:13:51,364
He broke right away.
He was ready to give it up. Needed to.

189
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:55,734
One-party consent call
implicating Maury Levy.

190
00:13:56,704 --> 00:13:59,264
- Where's Gary now?
- He went up to the second floor

191
00:13:59,306 --> 00:14:02,537
to hand in his letter of resignation
and went home to wait for the sword to drop.

192
00:14:02,576 --> 00:14:05,704
He's OK, he's better than you'd think.

193
00:14:07,381 --> 00:14:11,681
You know, if we can turn Levy
and some of these other drug lawyers,

194
00:14:11,719 --> 00:14:14,381
we can route the drug money all over town.

195
00:14:15,823 --> 00:14:17,688
It's sad business, I know,

196
00:14:17,725 --> 00:14:20,057
but at least we know the truth now, right?

197
00:14:21,228 --> 00:14:22,991
The truth, you say?

198
00:14:32,172 --> 00:14:33,833
Duquan, hello.

199
00:14:33,874 --> 00:14:35,307
Snatch-pops.

200
00:14:35,342 --> 00:14:37,776
Damien. You lost your mind?

201
00:14:37,811 --> 00:14:39,438
- But I said snatch-pops.
- I don't care.

202
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:41,038
You're gonna buy him a new sandwich,

203
00:14:41,081 --> 00:14:43,914
and past that, you're gonna ask
Mr. Williams for a broom

204
00:14:43,951 --> 00:14:45,384
to clean that up, you understand?

205
00:14:45,419 --> 00:14:49,515
Right now or you're mine
for another week of detention.

206
00:14:49,556 --> 00:14:51,353
I don't want to hear another word.

207
00:14:54,328 --> 00:14:56,296
It looks like you got the hang of it.

208
00:14:57,531 --> 00:14:59,431
What's up with you?

209
00:14:59,466 --> 00:15:01,627
Ain't nothing.

210
00:15:01,668 --> 00:15:03,499
You still at Southwestern?

211
00:15:03,537 --> 00:15:06,995
Well, I'm, like, needing a semester off,
you know?

212
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:10,005
I'm outdoors now.

213
00:15:11,612 --> 00:15:13,409
And...

214
00:15:13,447 --> 00:15:16,814
I was hoping maybe I could get with you

215
00:15:16,850 --> 00:15:20,377
and borrow some money,
so I can get a place and some clean clothes

216
00:15:20,421 --> 00:15:23,288
and get myself settled
so I can go back to school.

217
00:15:24,625 --> 00:15:25,922
You're on the street?

218
00:15:25,959 --> 00:15:28,519
I got people ready
to give me a really good place

219
00:15:28,562 --> 00:15:30,655
if I can come up
with some money for it.

220
00:15:34,668 --> 00:15:36,499
How much do you need?

221
00:15:36,537 --> 00:15:38,266
Couple of hundred.

222
00:15:38,305 --> 00:15:40,034
But if you could go one fifty more,

223
00:15:40,073 --> 00:15:44,203
I can enrol in the G.E.D. Program
down B.C.C.C.,

224
00:15:44,244 --> 00:15:47,042
then I could get my G.E.D.
Without having to go back to Southwestern.

225
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:49,071
Then I can get my work permit.

226
00:15:50,584 --> 00:15:53,576
I don't think you're eligible
for a G.E.D. Program

227
00:15:53,620 --> 00:15:56,248
if you're still of age to attend high school.

228
00:15:57,024 --> 00:15:58,685
Yeah, you are.

229
00:16:00,794 --> 00:16:02,523
I'll tell you what.

230
00:16:02,563 --> 00:16:05,361
Give me a couple minutes,
I'll drive you down there.

231
00:16:05,399 --> 00:16:08,664
If you are eligible, I'll write a check
right to the bursar's office.

232
00:16:08,702 --> 00:16:10,636
No, Mr. P., you ain't got to go through all that.

233
00:16:10,671 --> 00:16:13,640
Besides, I ain't got the time
to go down there today.

234
00:16:13,674 --> 00:16:15,574
But, you know, I'm gonna.

235
00:16:18,545 --> 00:16:20,877
I can do it, if that's what you want.

236
00:16:23,083 --> 00:16:25,381
And I don't even care about the money.

237
00:16:25,419 --> 00:16:29,082
But understand I'm gonna go down
to B.C.C.C. In a few days

238
00:16:29,122 --> 00:16:31,113
and find out if you're enrolled.

239
00:16:31,658 --> 00:16:33,922
And if you are, I'm gonna say, "Great.

240
00:16:33,961 --> 00:16:37,124
"Duquan can come past
with his certificate when he gets it,

241
00:16:37,164 --> 00:16:39,394
