stuff on the page there.

315
00:22:00,086 --> 00:22:02,987
Really makes me feel like
I know this guy and his world.

316
00:22:03,023 --> 00:22:05,389
You just pulled it all through the keyhole.

317
00:22:05,425 --> 00:22:06,551
Thanks, Gus.

318
00:22:06,593 --> 00:22:09,494
We get some good art,
I'm gonna push for the Sunday front.

319
00:22:09,529 --> 00:22:11,827
Well, I gotta make sure
the guy is good with it.

320
00:22:11,865 --> 00:22:13,025
What do you mean?

321
00:22:13,066 --> 00:22:14,590
The part of the story
about the kid bothers him.

322
00:22:14,634 --> 00:22:16,625
When he told me about it,
he was just talking...

323
00:22:16,670 --> 00:22:18,433
You told him you were
writing about him?

324
00:22:18,471 --> 00:22:21,031
I know, but...
I'm putting the guy's life out there.

325
00:22:21,074 --> 00:22:24,202
I wanna feel clean about it.
You know what I'm sayin'?

326
00:22:24,244 --> 00:22:25,939
I remember clean.

327
00:22:28,048 --> 00:22:31,950
Obviously, they're not in a hurry to go public
'cause we ain't cuffed.

328
00:22:31,985 --> 00:22:35,421
They're pretending on this case
like we're pretending. Why?

329
00:22:37,324 --> 00:22:40,316
Carcetti. He's exposed on this.

330
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:43,659
How? Just blame it all on us,
on the department.

331
00:22:43,697 --> 00:22:46,063
To kill us, they'd have to kill Rawls, Daniels

332
00:22:46,099 --> 00:22:48,329
and half the chain of command.
And he made those guys.

333
00:22:48,368 --> 00:22:50,199
It's his police department.

334
00:22:50,237 --> 00:22:54,071
So he opens himself up
right when he's out there, running for governor.

335
00:22:54,708 --> 00:22:58,508
So they want us to do what?
Run it down quietly? That's no problem.

336
00:22:58,545 --> 00:23:00,570
Six months from now, after the election,

337
00:23:00,614 --> 00:23:03,139
