372
00:24:49,522 --> 00:24:51,649
- They can do that?
- They can try.

373
00:24:51,691 --> 00:24:53,750
Depends on which judge they draw.

374
00:24:55,228 --> 00:24:58,391
So they ain't got no bail for Chris, right?
I mean, he got the murder one.

375
00:24:58,431 --> 00:24:59,796
Monk neither.

376
00:24:59,833 --> 00:25:02,734
Too much weight in his car
and he's on parole from the '04 charge.

377
00:25:02,769 --> 00:25:05,636
Best I could do was spring
Mr. Wagstaff on 300,000.

378
00:25:05,672 --> 00:25:07,606
- He show that kind of money?
- Put up his uncle's house

379
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:11,508
on surety bond for a third of it.
Bondsman is fronting the rest on a fake lien.

380
00:25:13,613 --> 00:25:18,516
Right now, the important thing is not bail,
the important thing is this...

381
00:25:18,551 --> 00:25:21,349
I need you to tell me
who else knew your clock code.

382
00:25:21,388 --> 00:25:22,980
I told you.

383
00:25:23,023 --> 00:25:26,652
Me, Cheese, Monk, Chris

384
00:25:26,693 --> 00:25:29,423
- and the supply. That's it.
- No one else?

385
00:25:29,462 --> 00:25:32,022
No one else even had my cell number,
except you.

386
00:25:36,603 --> 00:25:38,628
What?

387
00:25:38,671 --> 00:25:41,071
- There's a lie in here somewhere.
- I ain't lying.

388
00:25:41,107 --> 00:25:43,075
I don't mean you.

389
00:25:43,109 --> 00:25:45,600
Look, the police say the source told them

390
00:25:45,645 --> 00:25:47,340
