482
00:31:38,297 --> 00:31:40,060
White. Six foot.

483
00:31:40,099 --> 00:31:42,363
Not heavy, not skinny either.

484
00:31:43,035 --> 00:31:44,366
Clothes?

485
00:31:44,404 --> 00:31:46,372
Nothing I noticed. Kinda nondescript.

486
00:31:46,406 --> 00:31:48,601
Nondescript?

487
00:31:48,641 --> 00:31:52,168
I was surprised, I guess. I just thought,
"Whoa, what's he doing?"

488
00:31:52,211 --> 00:31:54,543
- Funny it being you to see this.
- It's weird.

489
00:31:54,580 --> 00:31:58,346
If an interview doesn't run late,
I'm not even here tonight.

490
00:31:58,384 --> 00:32:00,852
You mind if I get inside?
I gotta check in with my desk.

491
00:32:00,887 --> 00:32:03,014
You need anything else,
you got my number.

492
00:32:03,055 --> 00:32:04,784
Yeah.

493
00:32:09,662 --> 00:32:11,562
That guy's an asshole.

494
00:32:11,597 --> 00:32:13,792
This smokehound can't remember a thing.

495
00:32:13,833 --> 00:32:15,698
Only motherfucker
he remembers messing with him

496
00:32:15,735 --> 00:32:17,168
is the fella that found him.

497
00:32:17,203 --> 00:32:20,502
Whatever happened before that
is anyone's guess.

498
00:32:23,376 --> 00:32:26,834
Someone try to kidnap you,
drag you into a van?

499
00:32:26,879 --> 00:32:29,780
- OK.
- Who was trying to hurt you?

500
00:32:29,816 --> 00:32:32,546
My father. But he was a drunk.

501
00:32:32,585 --> 00:32:36,282
Detective, there's a vagrant over here
says he saw something.

502
00:32:39,292 --> 00:32:40,953
What did you see, fella?

503
00:32:46,899 --> 00:32:48,491
McNulty?

504
00:32:50,002 --> 00:32:52,732
- Johnny Weaver. Tactical.
- Fuck you. Why didn't you say so?

505
00:32:52,772 --> 00:32:54,763
J.W. Tryin' to keep your cover?

506
00:32:54,807 --> 00:32:58,265
It's better if everyone here
thinks I'm one of the regulars.

507
00:32:58,311 --> 00:33:00,074
Anyway, what's the ruckus with Petey?

508
00:33:00,112 --> 00:33:01,841
- The drunk?
- Yeah.

509
00:33:03,316 --> 00:33:05,546
Sun reporter says he's going into his building,

510
00:33:05,585 --> 00:33:08,247
he sees a guy trying to drag him
into a gray van.

511
00:33:08,287 --> 00:33:11,654
- It's bullshit, right?
- Yeah. Petey was laying there 45 minutes

512
00:33:11,691 --> 00:33:14,660
before that preppy cocksucker
even parks his car.

513
00:33:14,694 --> 00:33:16,218
- Thanks.
- No problem.

514
00:33:16,262 --> 00:33:18,025
Gimme a dollar, make it look right.

515
00:33:21,434 --> 00:33:23,299
Thank you, Jimmy.

516
00:33:24,837 --> 00:33:28,705
What about the reporter? You could charge
false statement, you know.

517
00:33:30,576 --> 00:33:34,273
You lock up every liar, there's no room
in B.D.C. For anyone else, right?

518
00:33:34,313 --> 00:33:36,247
More trouble than it's worth.

519
00:33:36,782 --> 00:33:38,682
Jay, it's horseshit. I'm going home.

520
00:33:38,718 --> 00:33:40,549
Yeah.

521
00:34:21,193 --> 00:34:23,388
Brought home some crabs.

522
00:34:23,429 --> 00:34:25,420
I already made dinner.

523
00:34:25,464 --> 00:34:28,194
Put 'em in the fridge.
Cold for lunch tomorrow, if you like.

524
00:34:28,234 --> 00:34:30,031
I can't eat 'em all.

525
00:34:41,948 --> 00:34:44,439
We don't run this shit,
especially not off the front.

526
00:34:44,483 --> 00:34:48,817
- I saw what I saw.
- Alma is on the phone with police P. I.O.

527
00:34:48,854 --> 00:34:50,845
And they are telling us on the record and off

528
00:34:50,890 --> 00:34:53,859
that they are discounting any report
of a possible abduction.

529
00:34:53,893 --> 00:34:56,726
That doesn't mean they're doing their job,
and it doesn't mean we...

530
00:34:56,762 --> 00:34:59,890
Our job is to report the news,
not to manufacture it.

531
00:34:59,932 --> 00:35:01,399
Fuck you, Gus.

532
00:35:03,302 --> 00:35:05,497
Nice.

533
00:35:11,777 --> 00:35:14,871
I know they're jealous of how much play
his stories get but the truth is...

534
00:35:14,914 --> 00:35:17,678
We cannot run this shit.

535
00:35:18,584 --> 00:35:21,553
Are you suggesting
that Scott made any of this up?

536
00:35:24,290 --> 00:35:26,918
You ever notice that the guys who do that,

537
00:35:27,426 --> 00:35:29,394
the Blairs, the Glasses, the Kelleys,

538
00:35:29,428 --> 00:35:31,328
they always start
with something small,

539
00:35:31,364 --> 00:35:35,095
just a little quote that they clean up.
And then it's a whole anecdote,

540
00:35:35,134 --> 00:35:38,069
and, pretty soon, they're seeing
some amazing shit.

541
00:35:38,638 --> 00:35:41,072
They're the lucky ones
who just happen to be standing

542
00:35:41,107 --> 00:35:44,702
on the right street corner in Tel Aviv
when the pizza joint blows up

543
00:35:44,744 --> 00:35:47,042
and the human head rolls down the street
with the eyes still blinking.

544
00:35:47,079 --> 00:35:50,480
The pictures were sent to him.
The police have confirmed...

545
00:35:50,516 --> 00:35:53,952
It always starts with something true,

546
00:35:53,986 --> 00:35:55,886
something confirmed.

547
00:35:55,921 --> 00:35:57,616
But then you've got a son of a bitch

548
00:35:57,657 --> 00:36:00,285
who just happens to be walking
in the Guilford entrance

549
00:36:00,326 --> 00:36:01,953
when the mysterious gray van comes...

550
00:36:01,994 --> 00:36:05,794
Gus, this has gotten personal
between you and Scott

551
00:36:05,831 --> 00:36:07,822
and it's affecting your judgment.

552
00:36:08,367 --> 00:36:10,733
I'm moving the story through the state desk.

553
00:36:10,770 --> 00:36:13,534
You should go home, think this through.

554
00:36:14,340 --> 00:36:16,001
We'll talk in the morning.

555
00:36:24,517 --> 00:36:26,781
Maybe you win a Pulitzer with this stuff

556
00:36:27,687 --> 00:36:29,621
and maybe you gotta give it back.

557
00:36:31,791 --> 00:36:34,282
It's in my notes, Gus.
Everything that happened,

558
00:36:34,326 --> 00:36:36,487
everything that guy said when I got to him.

559
00:36:36,529 --> 00:36:39,020
Every last word is in my notes.

560
00:37:01,253 --> 00:37:02,982
Home earlier than I thought.

561
00:37:03,556 --> 00:37:05,547
Yeah. Home.

562
00:37:20,539 --> 00:37:22,769
- He hit again.
- Who did?

563
00:37:22,808 --> 00:37:24,901
The serial killer.

564
00:37:24,944 --> 00:37:26,639
Get a grip, motherfucker.

565
00:37:26,679 --> 00:37:29,546
You don't believe me?
Check out his left wrist.

566
00:37:36,088 --> 00:37:38,079
You fuckin' with me again, Bunk?

567
00:37:39,692 --> 00:37:41,683
Copycat.

568
00:37:42,194 --> 00:37:44,094
Call McNulty. Get him down here.

569
00:37:53,472 --> 00:37:57,238
Been going over the charging documents
on the Partlow-Stanfield drug arrests.

570
00:37:57,276 --> 00:38:00,837
- Problematic to say the least.
- How so?

571
00:38:00,880 --> 00:38:02,507
They grab the phones and, minutes later,

572
00:38:02,548 --> 00:38:05,608
they've cracked an elaborate code
that implicates everyone.

573
00:38:05,651 --> 00:38:07,619
No one's that brilliant,

574
00:38:07,653 --> 00:38:09,280
not at the B.P.D., anyway.

575
00:38:10,723 --> 00:38:12,350
You don't know Lester Freamon.

576
00:38:12,391 --> 00:38:14,518
I know what I know.

577
00:38:14,560 --> 00:38:17,222
And this feels to me like an illegal wiretap.

578
00:38:17,897 --> 00:38:20,058
Your guys were on those phones,
tracking my clients

579
00:38:20,099 --> 00:38:23,125
- long before they went near any drugs.
- Untrue.

580
00:38:24,470 --> 00:38:26,597
We get into discovery
and I'm going to have no problem

581
00:38:26,639 --> 00:38:30,006
knocking down that bullshit
about a source of information.

582
00:38:30,042 --> 00:38:33,705
And my sources around here tell me that,
with all the budget cutbacks,

583
00:38:33,746 --> 00:38:36,237
the only wiretap
you all have had up this year

584
00:38:36,282 --> 00:38:38,773
has been on the homeless killer thing.

585
00:38:39,385 --> 00:38:41,717
Whatever else you're running is illegal.

586
00:38:42,555 --> 00:38:44,250
Sources?

587
00:38:44,290 --> 00:38:46,724
Title threes are supposed to be secret.

588
00:38:47,560 --> 00:38:51,189
Are you saying you have a source
of information inside the courthouse?

589
00:38:51,230 --> 00:38:53,221
It's a figure of speech.

590
00:38:53,833 --> 00:38:56,996
What I'm saying is that
there's shit in the blood of your case,

591
00:38:57,036 --> 00:38:59,732
and, if you wait until this goes past indictments,

592
00:38:59,772 --> 00:39:01,569
I'm gonna run wild with it.

593
00:39:03,175 --> 00:39:04,938
We should talk.

594
00:39:04,977 --> 00:39:06,501
Out of court.

595
00:39:09,982 --> 00:39:11,449
Fuck me.

596
00:39:13,419 --> 00:39:15,853
Is it enough? Do you have enough?

597
00:39:15,888 --> 00:39:18,516
It has to be. It should be.

598
00:39:18,557 --> 00:39:20,718
You can't look at everything
that Robert found,

599
00:39:20,759 --> 00:39:23,819
at the pattern, and not see
what this fucking guy's about.

600
00:39:23,863 --> 00:39:25,854
You know that. I know that.

601
00:39:26,899 --> 00:39:28,924
What, you don't think so?

602
00:39:28,968 --> 00:39:30,833
I think that if you do this,

603
00:39:30,870 --> 00:39:32,963
these son of a bitches will do you.

604
00:39:34,373 --> 00:39:35,931
Come.

605
00:39:35,975 --> 00:39:38,569
Sorry. There's been another homeless murder.

606
00:39:38,611 --> 00:39:40,306
South Baltimore.

607
00:39:42,348 --> 00:39:44,509
Careful, Gus.

608
00:39:44,550 --> 00:39:46,541
I can't protect you.

609
00:39:57,096 --> 00:39:59,724
- No fucking way.
- Dead for a while.

610
00:39:59,765 --> 00:40:03,326
And I can assume, Jimmy,
from the fact that the ribbon ain't red

611
00:40:03,369 --> 00:40:06,463
and the fact that you don't need another body
because Marlo is locked up...

612
00:40:06,505 --> 00:40:10,999
- I got nothing to do with this.
- Wonderful. We've eliminated one suspect.

613
00:40:11,043 --> 00:40:12,533
You see what you started here?

614
00:40:12,578 --> 00:40:15,308
The bosses are gonna toss it
back to you. No doubt.

615
00:40:15,347 --> 00:40:17,679
- The bosses know it's bullshit.
- What?

616
00:40:17,716 --> 00:40:21,049
- Daniels knows. Pearlman, too.
- How the fuck you?

617
00:40:23,756 --> 00:40:26,554
- How much longer does this...
- Can you give us a minute?

618
00:40:26,592 --> 00:40:29,493
You turning the world
upside down with your bullshit.

619
00:40:29,528 --> 00:40:31,393
- How are you not in jail?
- I don't know.

620
00:40:31,430 --> 00:40:33,489
The lie's so big, people can live with it.

621
00:40:33,532 --> 00:40:38,993
Jesus fucking Christ, Jimmy. I told you.
I fuckin' told you it was going to come to this.

622
00:40:39,772 --> 00:40:44,209
You played with fire, didn't you?
And now we're all getting burned...

623
00:40:45,277 --> 00:40:48,337
...reporting live from South Baltimore,
where police have found the body

624
00:40:48,380 --> 00:40:50,712
of what appears to be
another homeless man.

625
00:40:50,749 --> 00:40:54,116
This one killed and left in a vacant lot...

626
00:40:54,153 --> 00:40:56,553
...short while ago have refused so far...

627
00:40:56,588 --> 00:40:58,453
Did somebody not get the message?

628
00:41:36,962 --> 00:41:40,591
You're not killing them yourself, McNulty,
at least assure me of that.

629
00:41:44,737 --> 00:41:46,671
And the one you disappeared?

630
00:41:47,439 --> 00:41:49,771
He's OK, last I checked.

631
00:41:49,808 --> 00:41:53,938
Good. That's a start, I guess.

632
00:41:53,979 --> 00:41:57,471
- I thought you got a message.
- Copycat.

633
00:41:58,283 --> 00:42:00,274
I got nothing on this one.

634
00:42:00,853 --> 00:42:01,911
Jesus.

635
00:42:01,954 --> 00:42:05,549
How did you do it?
How did you get 'em by the medical examiner?

636
00:42:05,591 --> 00:42:08,719
Some were real and I just linked 'em
with the ribbons.

637
00:42:08,761 --> 00:42:10,592
Some I juked as strangle jobs.

638
00:42:13,632 --> 00:42:16,533
- If it matters, I know now...
- Fuck what you know now.

639
00:42:16,568 --> 00:42:20,902
This was all for money, McNulty?
You couldn't live without the O. T?

640
00:42:20,939 --> 00:42:23,806
The Stanfield case. It was that.

641
00:42:23,842 --> 00:42:26,834
I know where it went,
but you got paid, too.

642
00:42:26,879 --> 00:42:30,076
You and Freamon
and maybe a dozen other guys.

643
00:42:30,115 --> 00:42:32,106
It wasn't about the money.

644
00:42:40,893 --> 00:42:42,827
Down the road, when we settle on this,

645
00:42:42,861 --> 00:42:45,125
and we will settle on this,

646
00:42:45,164 --> 00:42:49,362
I don't expect any of you will ever see
another hour of O.T. Again.

647
00:42:49,401 --> 00:42:52,996
I don't expect any of you
will be doing police work ever again.

648
00:42:53,038 --> 00:42:55,768
And the only reason this isn't before
a grand jury right now

649
00:42:55,808 --> 00:42:58,675
is because our mayor can't live with that.

650
00:42:59,211 --> 00:43:02,374
Oh, yeah.
The Mayor knows your name.

651
00:43:02,414 --> 00:43:06,976
So this is your last case. Work it.

652
00:43:07,019 --> 00:43:09,112
If you're half the detective you think you are,

653
00:43:09,154 --> 00:43:12,282
you'll put this one down fast
and take us all off the hook.

654
00:43:12,324 --> 00:43:14,315
The longer this goes on,

655
00:43:14,359 --> 00:43:16,350
the worse the payback's gonna be.

656
00:43:34,446 --> 00:43:36,073
But what does he really know?

657
00:43:36,115 --> 00:43:39,846
What he knows now isn't half
of what he'll learn when we get to discovery.

658
00:43:39,885 --> 00:43:42,945
They won't be able to produce
a credible source of information.

659
00:43:42,988 --> 00:43:46,617
They don't have to if it's not a registered C. I.
A source is only...

660
00:43:46,658 --> 00:43:48,853
If he can raise doubts in a judge's mind,

661
00:43:48,894 --> 00:43:51,192
we could be compelled to reveal our source.

662
00:43:51,230 --> 00:43:53,425
At that point, we're giving up the wiretap.

663
00:43:53,465 --> 00:43:55,660
And he gets the paperwork
from the phone company.

664
00:43:55,701 --> 00:43:57,692
Which has Stanfield's number on it.

665
00:43:58,403 --> 00:44:00,462
God.

666
00:44:01,073 --> 00:44:03,803
The only thing we can do is barter.

667
00:44:03,842 --> 00:44:05,673
Then barter. This can't go to court.

668
00:44:05,711 --> 00:44:07,269
We do have some leverage.

669
00:44:08,213 --> 00:44:10,078
What?

670
00:44:11,016 --> 00:44:14,918
Let's just say Mr. Levy has problems
of his own to deal with.

671
00:44:16,155 --> 00:44:18,146
Make this go away...

672
00:44:18,824 --> 00:44:21,486
and the Mayor will not forget that you did so.

673
00:44:22,661 --> 00:44:24,356
Nor will I.

674
00:44:26,965 --> 00:44:29,433
Jimmy, ass up an' help us with this.

675
00:44:31,003 --> 00:44:32,834
Shit is funky.

676
00:44:37,109 --> 00:44:41,205
- We should take this into the box.
- Where's the pocket contents?

677
00:44:41,246 --> 00:44:44,682
We have questions
about the reported kidnapping...

678
00:44:44,716 --> 00:44:46,911
- Those two bags there.
- Yes, ma'am.

679
00:44:48,820 --> 00:44:51,288
Well, that would seem
to be the newspaper's problem.

680
00:44:52,658 --> 00:44:55,252
I get another fucking call about a gray van,

681
00:44:55,294 --> 00:44:58,695
I'm burning that fucking newspaper building
to the ground.

682
00:45:00,399 --> 00:45:02,196
What?

683
00:45:04,836 --> 00:45:07,669
Your homeless guy from days ago,
what was in his pockets?

684
00:45:07,706 --> 00:45:10,937
- Bullshit.
- You got business cards?

685
00:45:10,976 --> 00:45:12,637
Yeah, but every card has an alibi.

686
00:45:12,678 --> 00:45:15,340
- Let me see.
- I thought we were done with this.

687
00:45:25,958 --> 00:45:27,949
So, where you going with this?

688
00:45:30,262 --> 00:45:33,493
- I think it's down.
- Motherfucker, you ain't that good.

689
00:45:35,267 --> 00:45:37,565
McNulty, what's up with this?

690
00:45:40,906 --> 00:45:42,635
You OK, Gus?

691
00:45:45,444 --> 00:45:47,173
Yeah, I'm good.

692
00:45:55,687 --> 00:45:57,211
What?

693
00:45:59,958 --> 00:46:01,653
Alma, what's up?

694
00:46:03,996 --> 00:46:06,191
- It's empty.
- What's empty?

695
00:46:06,231 --> 00:46:09,962
The pad he waved at you,
saying it was all filled with notes.

696
00:46:11,136 --> 00:46:13,104
It's empty. Every page.

697
00:46:15,007 --> 00:46:16,736
Thanks.

698
00:46:37,362 --> 00:46:39,557
What the fuck is that about?

699
00:46:49,107 --> 00:46:51,405
Alma, TV has police on a sweep
of the homeless

700
00:46:51,443 --> 00:46:53,968
under Hanover street.

701
00:47:01,520 --> 00:47:03,283
I'll get right to the point.

702
00:47:03,322 --> 00:47:04,914
Please do.

703
00:47:09,027 --> 00:47:12,463
- You have Stanfield, right? He's your client?
- Yeah, him and his people.

704
00:47:12,497 --> 00:47:14,294
I have some stuff,
straight from the grand jury

705
00:47:14,333 --> 00:47:16,893
that you're gonna wanna
see sooner rather than later.

706
00:47:16,935 --> 00:47:19,733
- Is this a title three case?
- You'll find it interesting, I promise.

707
00:47:19,771 --> 00:47:23,434
- All right. When can you meet?
- Tomorrow, after work. Same money, right?

708
00:47:23,475 --> 00:47:25,636
- Yeah, the money's the same.
- Good.

709
00:47:28,914 --> 00:47:31,849
We can grand jury
Gary diPasquale tomorrow,

710
00:47:31,883 --> 00:47:34,647
along with that one-party consent call.

711
00:47:34,686 --> 00:47:35,812
Or...

712
00:47:37,356 --> 00:47:39,017
here's the deal.

713
00:47:39,524 --> 00:47:41,583
No court trials.

714
00:47:41,626 --> 00:47:45,960
Partlow pleads to all of the bodies
in the vacants and takes life, no parole.

715
00:47:45,997 --> 00:47:49,524
We'd want the second shooter, too,
but Pearson's beyond that now.

716
00:47:49,568 --> 00:47:53,026
Metcalf and Wagstaff plead
to possession with intent.

717
00:47:53,071 --> 00:47:55,301
Stanfield takes ten years on conspiracy.

718
00:47:57,242 --> 00:47:59,904
You're blackmailing an officer of the court.

719
00:47:59,945 --> 00:48:03,403
The moment you came in here
and offered that quid pro quo,

720
00:48:03,448 --> 00:48:05,882
you were guilty of obstruction of justice.

721
00:48:05,917 --> 00:48:07,782
You're right.

722
00:48:08,353 --> 00:48:10,480
I could get six to eight years.

723
00:48:11,923 --> 00:48:16,690
And for bribery of a state's attorney
and the violation of grand jury secrecy,

724
00:48:16,728 --> 00:48:18,491
you could see ten to twelve.

725
00:48:20,198 --> 00:48:23,167
I'll be out a couple years before you.

726
00:48:23,201 --> 00:48:25,999
You come home,
first round's on me, I guess.

727
00:48:26,037 --> 00:48:29,666
So you'll let me walk
to keep this case out of open court?

728
00:48:29,708 --> 00:48:32,871
That file must be dirty as hell.

729
00:48:32,911 --> 00:48:35,846
The conspiracy charge on Stanfield falls
without the cellphones

730
00:48:35,881 --> 00:48:38,543
and you and I both know
that if someone does some digging,

731
00:48:38,583 --> 00:48:42,075
they're gonna find an illegal wiretap
and you're gonna lose the phones.

732
00:48:42,120 --> 00:48:44,588
Everhart, 274,

733
