975
01:06:00,424 --> 01:06:02,722
He was the black sheep,

976
01:06:03,727 --> 01:06:05,661
the permanent pariah.

977
01:06:06,163 --> 01:06:08,927
He asked no quarter of the bosses
and none was given.

978
01:06:08,966 --> 01:06:10,900
He learned no lessons,

979
01:06:11,335 --> 01:06:13,326
he acknowledged no mistakes.

980
01:06:13,370 --> 01:06:15,304
He was as stubborn a Mick as ever stumbled

981
01:06:15,339 --> 01:06:18,467
out of the Northeast parishes
to take a patrolman's shield.

982
01:06:18,509 --> 01:06:20,204
He brooked no authority.

983
01:06:20,244 --> 01:06:23,941
He did what he wanted to do
and he said what he wanted to say

984
01:06:23,981 --> 01:06:27,508
and, in the end,
he gave you the clearances.

985
01:06:29,019 --> 01:06:32,045
- He's natural police.
- Yes, he was.

986
01:06:32,089 --> 01:06:35,388
I don't say that about many people,
even when they're here on the felt.

987
01:06:35,426 --> 01:06:38,054
I don't give that one up
unless it happens to be true.

988
01:06:39,296 --> 01:06:41,093
Natural poh-leece.

989
01:06:50,941 --> 01:06:52,704
But Christ, what an asshole.

990
01:06:56,413 --> 01:07:00,907
And I'm not talkin' about the ordinary,
gaping orifice that all of us possess.

991
01:07:00,951 --> 01:07:04,910
I mean an all-encompassing,
all-consuming,

992
01:07:04,955 --> 01:07:08,584
out of proportion to every other facet
of his humanity chasm.

993
01:07:09,260 --> 01:07:11,785
From whose borne,
if I may quote Shakespeare,

994
01:07:11,829 --> 01:07:13,626
no traveler has ever returned.

995
01:07:13,664 --> 01:07:16,189
- The fuck did I do?
- Shut the fuck up.

996
01:07:16,233 --> 01:07:18,224
You're dead to us now.

997
01:07:20,538 --> 01:07:22,529
Here's his partner in crime.

998
01:07:26,310 --> 01:07:28,801
Now, now. Be gentle. Be gentle.

999
01:07:28,846 --> 01:07:30,837
I'm a civilian now. Be gentle.

1000
01:07:30,881 --> 01:07:32,849
Your papers went in?

1001
01:07:32,883 --> 01:07:36,444
- Yeah, this afternoon. 32 years.
- And four months.

1002
01:07:38,722 --> 01:07:41,020
Y'all did a fine job with him, you did.

1003
01:07:41,058 --> 01:07:44,323
He look to be about ten years younger
than I remember.

1004
01:07:44,361 --> 01:07:48,092
Well, c'mon, there's enough room
for both of you to be laid out.

1005
01:07:50,734 --> 01:07:52,793
One at a time.

1006
01:07:52,836 --> 01:07:54,895
You don't crowd a man at his own wake.

1007
01:07:56,273 --> 01:07:58,605
Come on, Lester. Come and snuggle.

1008
01:07:59,577 --> 01:08:03,411
Keep our secrets, Jimmy.
I got Shardene with me tonight.

1009
01:08:03,447 --> 01:08:07,781
If you gentlemen will spare us
this unfortunate homoerotic lapse,

1010
01:08:07,818 --> 01:08:09,877
I will conclude my elegiac remarks.

1011
01:08:09,920 --> 01:08:12,286
Then do it, you gabby motherfucker.

1012
01:08:13,324 --> 01:08:15,724
To conclude. To conclude,

1013
01:08:15,759 --> 01:08:18,887
I say he gave us 13 years on the line.

1014
01:08:19,463 --> 01:08:23,229
Not enough for a pension
but enough for us to know that he was...

1015
01:08:23,267 --> 01:08:24,996
Put the fucking song on.

1016
01:08:25,035 --> 01:08:27,503
...despite his negligible Irish ancestry,

1017
01:08:27,538 --> 01:08:29,563
his defects of personality,

1018
01:08:29,607 --> 01:08:33,043
and his inconstant sobriety and hygiene,

1019
01:08:35,279 --> 01:08:37,372
a true murder police.

1020
01:08:40,718 --> 01:08:42,652
I say this seriously.

1021
01:08:43,654 --> 01:08:46,145
If I was laying there dead
on some Baltimore street corner,

1022
01:08:46,190 --> 01:08:49,057
I'd want it to be you standing over me,
catching the case.

1023
01:08:49,093 --> 01:08:50,754
Bullshit.

1024
01:08:53,931 --> 01:08:58,197
Because, brother, when you were good,
you were the best we had.

1025
01:09:00,571 --> 01:09:05,099
Shit, if you was lying there dead on some
corner, it was probably Jimmy that done ya.

1026
01:09:06,210 --> 01:09:08,075
Fuck you! If you caught the case,

1027
01:09:08,112 --> 01:09:10,376
you'd be standing there pissing in my ear.

1028
01:10:32,329 --> 01:10:34,593
How did Nerese Campbell get it?

1029
01:10:34,631 --> 01:10:37,828
You think I asked?
Do you think it even matters?

1030
01:10:37,868 --> 01:10:41,565
She gave it to me because
she thought you'd listen to me.

1031
01:10:41,605 --> 01:10:43,630
So now they want me to go.

1032
01:10:44,341 --> 01:10:47,071
The way she expressed it
is that she wanted you to stay

1033
01:10:47,111 --> 01:10:48,942
if you could come to your senses.

1034
01:10:48,979 --> 01:10:50,970
Come to my senses.

1035
01:10:52,683 --> 01:10:56,619
She wants me to juke the stats for Carcetti,
this quarter and the next,

1036
01:10:56,653 --> 01:10:58,951
hide the crime,
get him elected as governor

1037
01:10:58,989 --> 01:11:01,549
and make her the Mayor.

1038
01:11:01,592 --> 01:11:03,992
So do it.
Burrell juked them before you.

1039
01:11:04,027 --> 01:11:05,585
Warren Frasier before him.

1040
01:11:05,629 --> 01:11:09,622
And, after you're gone,
Rawls or whoever will juke them. So what?

1041
01:11:09,666 --> 01:11:12,157
I'll swallow a lie when I have to.

1042
01:11:12,202 --> 01:11:14,295
I've swallowed a few big ones lately.

1043
01:11:15,239 --> 01:11:20,142
But the stat games, that lie,
it's what ruined this department.

1044
01:11:20,177 --> 01:11:22,304
Shining up shit and calling it gold,

1045
01:11:22,346 --> 01:11:25,076
so majors become colonels
and mayors become governors.

1046
01:11:25,115 --> 01:11:28,516
Pretending to do police work
while one generation fucking trains the next

1047
01:11:28,552 --> 01:11:30,986
how not to do the job. And then...

1048
01:11:35,659 --> 01:11:37,650
I looked Carcetti in the eye.

1049
01:11:38,362 --> 01:11:41,195
I shook his hand.
I asked him if he was for real.

1050
01:11:42,599 --> 01:11:44,624
This is the lie I can't live with.

1051
01:11:45,335 --> 01:11:48,896
If I do, then Nerese has me in her pocket
whenever she wants me.

1052
01:11:48,939 --> 01:11:51,908
And I'm no good to anyone like that.

1053
01:11:51,942 --> 01:11:53,807
Then go.

1054
01:11:53,844 --> 01:11:57,780
Withdraw for personal reasons
or health reasons.

1055
01:11:57,815 --> 01:11:59,282
Whatever.

1056
01:11:59,316 --> 01:12:02,308
You've got your law degree.
You're not gonna starve.

1057
01:12:04,021 --> 01:12:07,184
But if you don't go,
they'll wreck both of us.

1058
01:12:07,224 --> 01:12:09,419
There's not enough in here to indict me.

1059
01:12:09,459 --> 01:12:11,256
And the joke of it is,

1060
01:12:11,295 --> 01:12:14,787
I've seen enough the last few days
to have them indicted.

1061
01:12:14,832 --> 01:12:16,697
For what?

1062
01:12:17,434 --> 01:12:20,665
Then use it, Cedric, or at least threaten to.

1063
01:12:20,704 --> 01:12:22,672
People will get hurt.

1064
01:12:23,841 --> 01:12:25,502
People I care about.

1065
01:12:27,544 --> 01:12:30,513
Then you're done.
There's enough in that file

1066
01:12:30,547 --> 01:12:32,879
that you'll never make it
through confirmation hearings.

1067
01:12:32,916 --> 01:12:36,750
And enough so that my career is dead
before it even gets started.

1068
01:12:41,058 --> 01:12:43,492
The tree that doesn't bend breaks, Cedric.

1069
01:12:44,228 --> 01:12:47,095
Bend too far, you're already broken.

1070
01:12:48,966 --> 01:12:50,934
Marlo on a walk.

1071
01:12:52,369 --> 01:12:55,133
And the money,
she gave that away, too.

1072
01:12:56,673 --> 01:12:58,641
Yeah.

1073
01:12:58,675 --> 01:13:00,609
We don't get to follow the money.

1074
01:13:04,715 --> 01:13:06,808
Hey, wonderin' where you was.

1075
01:13:06,850 --> 01:13:09,148
I didn't know if I should come out on this here.

1076
01:13:09,186 --> 01:13:11,245
Why the fuck not?

1077
01:13:11,288 --> 01:13:12,983
Was me who told Daniels.

1078
01:13:15,492 --> 01:13:18,950
I didn't want to do it behind your back but...

1079
01:13:18,996 --> 01:13:20,793
it had to be done.

1080
01:13:27,704 --> 01:13:31,800
Anyway, it was great being on the job with y'all.

1081
01:13:33,877 --> 01:13:35,970
I just wanted to say that too, I guess.

1082
01:13:37,047 --> 01:13:38,810
So what?

1083
01:13:38,849 --> 01:13:40,942
You ain't gonna drink with me?

1084
01:13:42,819 --> 01:13:44,912
I am if you want.

1085
01:13:46,823 --> 01:13:48,381
Detective,

1086
01:13:49,092 --> 01:13:51,253
if you think it needed doing...

1087
01:13:51,295 --> 01:13:53,024
I guess it did.

1088
01:14:00,437 --> 01:14:02,268
You coming?

1089
01:14:22,326 --> 01:14:24,157
Milton came with 600.

1090
01:14:25,062 --> 01:14:26,859
And Little Glen is in for three.

1091
01:14:26,897 --> 01:14:28,728
I got five from me

1092
01:14:28,765 --> 01:14:31,359
and I got five from Chinaman to cover.

1093
01:14:31,401 --> 01:14:34,598
- We still short 900.
- I can go that. No thing.

1094
01:14:34,638 --> 01:14:37,368
What? Motherfucker, where you get
that kind of scratch?

1095
01:14:37,407 --> 01:14:39,102
You don't think Cheese know this here game?

1096
01:14:39,142 --> 01:14:42,339
We sellin' dope an' coke in Baltimore, nigger,

1097
01:14:42,379 --> 01:14:45,280
any of y'all ain't got that kind of money
need be ashamed.

1098
01:14:45,315 --> 01:14:48,614
You still puttin' up more
than your share with that.

1099
01:14:49,052 --> 01:14:52,385
The way I look at it,
we all gonna be more than paid

1100
01:14:52,422 --> 01:14:54,083
once we own the connect, so...

1101
01:14:54,124 --> 01:14:56,786
Shit, nigger, we was good
when your uncle had it.

1102
01:14:56,827 --> 01:14:59,091
You had to go ahead and put up with Marlo.

1103
01:14:59,997 --> 01:15:02,090
See that? See now,

1104
01:15:02,132 --> 01:15:04,327
that's just the wrong way to look at it

1105
01:15:04,368 --> 01:15:07,997
'cause Joe had his time
and Omar put an end to that.

1106
01:15:08,038 --> 01:15:10,563
Then Marlo had his time,
short as it was,

1107
01:15:10,607 --> 01:15:12,541
and the police put an end to that.

1108
01:15:12,576 --> 01:15:15,238
And now, motherfucker, it's our time.

1109
01:15:15,278 --> 01:15:17,746
Mines and yours.

1110
01:15:17,781 --> 01:15:20,443
But instead of just shutting up and kicking in,

1111
01:15:20,484 --> 01:15:23,317
you gonna stand there cryin'
that back-in-the-day shit.

1112
01:15:23,353 --> 01:15:25,446
There ain't no back in the day, nigger.

1113
01:15:25,489 --> 01:15:27,855
Ain't no nostalgia to this shit here.

1114
01:15:29,059 --> 01:15:32,358
There's just the street and the game

1115
01:15:32,396 --> 01:15:34,125
and what happen here today.

1116
01:15:34,164 --> 01:15:35,961
You right.

1117
01:15:40,470 --> 01:15:43,769
When it was my uncle,
I was with my uncle.

1118
01:15:43,807 --> 01:15:46,435
When it was Marlo,
I was with him.

1119
01:15:46,476 --> 01:15:48,341
But now, nigger...

1120
01:15:54,084 --> 01:15:56,450
What the fuck did you do that for?

1121
01:15:56,486 --> 01:15:58,886
Now we short the nine.

1122
01:15:58,922 --> 01:16:00,617
That was for Joe.

1123
01:16:02,492 --> 01:16:05,893
This sentimental motherfucker
just cost us money.

1124
01:17:45,228 --> 01:17:46,957
Hey, Alma...

1125
01:17:55,038 --> 01:17:56,938
I just heard.

1126
01:17:57,474 --> 01:18:00,443
The Carroll County bureau?
That's how they punish me?

1127
01:18:00,477 --> 01:18:03,139
Why not just send my ass
all the way to Pennsylvania?

1128
01:18:03,180 --> 01:18:05,114
What'd they tell you?

1129
01:18:05,148 --> 01:18:09,050
That I did an excellent job,
that this had nothing to do with anything

1130
01:18:09,085 --> 01:18:12,077
but trying to make
the county bureaus stronger.

1131
01:18:13,957 --> 01:18:17,791
Alma, I didn't tell them about the notepad.
I left that part out.

1132
01:18:17,827 --> 01:18:21,729
I told them. When I heard you were in trouble,
I went to Whiting,

1133
01:18:21,765 --> 01:18:25,599
told him I thought you were right about Scott.
I told him about the notepad.

1134
01:18:25,635 --> 01:18:27,660
Did he make all of it up?

1135
01:18:27,704 --> 01:18:32,004
- The calls from the killer? The pictures?
- Some, not all.

1136
01:18:33,343 --> 01:18:35,504
- Why?
- Look around.

1137
01:18:37,180 --> 01:18:38,738
The pond is shrinking.

1138
01:18:38,782 --> 01:18:41,182
The fish are nervous.

1139
01:18:41,218 --> 01:18:43,209
Get some profile, win a prize,

1140
01:18:43,253 --> 01:18:45,949
maybe find a bigger pond somewhere.

1141
01:18:45,989 --> 01:18:48,219
Whiting, Klebanow, Templeton...

1142
01:18:49,826 --> 01:18:54,126
They snatch a Pulitzer or two
and they are up and gone from this place.

1143
01:18:54,564 --> 01:18:56,623
For them, that's what this is all about.

1144
01:18:57,234 --> 01:18:59,896
Me? I'm too fucking simpleminded for that.

1145
01:19:01,171 --> 01:19:05,267
I just wanted to see
something new every day

1146
01:19:05,308 --> 01:19:06,741
and write a story with it.

1147
01:19:09,279 --> 01:19:13,409
Alma, you'll write your way
outta Carroll in no time, watch.

1148
01:19:13,450 --> 01:19:17,352
About as fast as you edit your way
off the copy desk?

1149
01:19:34,604 --> 01:19:36,595
Congratulations, Sergeant Goette.

1150
01:19:37,207 --> 01:19:39,141
I know you'll do well in the Eastern.

1151
01:19:43,380 --> 01:19:47,612
Glad I got to do this at least.
Congratulations, Lieutenant Carver.

1152
01:19:47,651 --> 01:19:52,247
Thank you, sir. I'm just sorry
it won't be you I'm serving under.

1153
01:19:52,289 --> 01:19:54,154
Word gets around?

1154
01:19:54,190 --> 01:19:56,317
It's on W.B.A.L. Today.

1155
01:19:56,359 --> 01:19:59,226
They said you're leaving for family reasons.

1156
01:19:59,262 --> 01:20:02,629
I guess I got some kids
somewhere I don't even know about.

1157
01:20:02,666 --> 01:20:04,531
They say on B.A.L. Who they're sending up

1158
01:20:04,567 --> 01:20:06,899
- as acting commissioner?
- Say it ain't so.

1159
01:20:11,841 --> 01:20:14,002
Ladies and gentlemen,

1160
01:20:14,044 --> 01:20:18,674
as what may be my last official act
as a Baltimore police officer,

1161
01:20:18,715 --> 01:20:21,582
allow me to congratulate
all of the promoted officers,

1162
01:20:21,618 --> 01:20:25,349
their families, their fellow officers
and their friends.

1163
01:20:33,430 --> 01:20:37,594
You ain't careful, they may make you major,
then you'll be truly fucked.

1164
01:20:37,634 --> 01:20:38,931
- Good job.
- Thanks.

1165
01:20:38,968 --> 01:20:40,367
- Proud of you.
- Thanks.

1166
01:20:56,986 --> 01:21:01,446
See now, there you go, giving a fuck
when it ain't your turn to give a fuck.

1167
01:21:01,491 --> 01:21:04,119
- Lehman's squad was up.
- I needed the O.T.

1168
01:21:04,160 --> 01:21:06,822
Yeah, now you got a shooting with no wits,

1169
01:21:06,863 --> 01:21:10,196
no suspect and no prayer
of it going to black.

1170
01:21:10,233 --> 01:21:12,201
Picking up the phone
like a goddamn rookie. Shame on you.

1171
01:21:12,235 --> 01:21:14,760
Stop squealin' like a bitch.

1172
01:21:14,804 --> 01:21:17,136
An' make sure you don't step
on that shell casing behind you.

1173
01:21:17,173 --> 01:21:19,801
I ain't gonna kick no shell casings behind me.
It's there on the side.

1174
01:21:19,843 --> 01:21:24,303
I'm gonna step back and kick no shell casing
you don't mark with letters and numbers.

1175
01:21:27,884 --> 01:21:30,876
I understand.
And you gotta be in the system.

1176
01:21:30,920 --> 01:21:33,946
- They sent you the form.
- They told me that wasn't good enough.

1177
01:21:33,990 --> 01:21:35,981
They said they wanted the other paperwork.

1178
01:21:36,025 --> 01:21:39,119
- And you applied for S.S. I., Mr. Belton?
- Yes, ma'am.

1179
01:21:39,162 --> 01:21:41,926
Well, let's go inside
and look it up on the computer.

1180
01:21:41,965 --> 01:21:43,364
Hey, you remember me?

1181
01:21:44,768 --> 01:21:49,535
I brought this guy in a few weeks back,
just wanted to see how he was.

1182
01:21:49,572 --> 01:21:52,405
He wandered out after a couple nights.

1183
01:21:52,442 --> 01:21:54,034
Sorry.

1184
01:21:55,211 --> 01:21:57,202
Where...

1185
01:21:57,247 --> 01:22:01,308
- Where do the homeless go around here?
- Different places. Down by the river,

1186
01:22:01,351 --> 01:22:03,342
over in the warehouse district.

1187
01:22:04,687 --> 01:22:07,554
Some of the places I don't think
it would be safe for you to go.

1188
01:22:07,590 --> 01:22:10,286
I'm police. Well, I used to be.

1189
01:22:10,326 --> 01:22:12,487
Wait here. I'll see if I can find you a map.

1190
01:22:12,529 --> 01:22:14,793
- Thanks.
- Come on, Mr. Belton.

1191
01:22:18,601 --> 01:22:20,466
...and if the major could find his ass
with his hand,

1192
01:22:20,503 --> 01:22:23,472
he'd know that we have more than enough
to be up on a pen register.

1193
01:22:23,506 --> 01:22:25,167
Lieutenant Carver told him so.

1194
01:22:25,208 --> 01:22:28,336
But fuck if he isn't trying
to shut this thing down.

1195
01:22:32,615 --> 01:22:35,607
Alls I'm sayin' is a phone call or two
and you're gonna find out

1196
01:22:35,652 --> 01:22:38,712
that they're getting some kinda pressure
from somewhere to sit on this thing,

1197
01:22:38,755 --> 01:22:41,553
even though we've tied three killings
to this crew.

1198
01:22:42,926 --> 01:22:45,190
Does the Police Commissioner know?

1199
01:22:45,228 --> 01:22:49,688
Him? He wouldn't know police work
if it took down his front door on a warrant.

1200
01:22:54,504 --> 01:22:57,701
Just... keep my name out of it.

1201
01:23:00,343 --> 01:23:03,437
New Westport is like Howard Street
ten years ago,

1202
01:23:03,480 --> 01:23:05,175
except the land's cheaper

1203
01:23:05,215 --> 01:23:08,207
and there's more potential for mixed use
because of the waterfront location.

1204
01:23:08,251 --> 01:23:11,687
- There you are.
- You can't put a price on a water view.

1205
01:23:11,721 --> 01:23:13,746
Yes, you can.

1206
01:23:13,790 --> 01:23:15,655
You definitely can.

1207
01:23:15,692 --> 01:23:18,559
Andy, he's gotta meet Tommy
and they're leaving early

1208
01:23:18,595 --> 01:23:20,085
so let me borrow him for a moment.

1209
01:23:20,129 --> 01:23:23,155
Sure, no problem.
Nice to meet you, Mr. Stanfield.

1210
01:23:25,902 --> 01:23:27,893
You know who you were talking to?

1211
